class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qxl1719657689828.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qxl1719657689828.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ppd1665702781928\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ppd1665702781928___atan_252995\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the arc tangent of X.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__topic_d80519e1_d80520e1_d80521e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__p_d80522e1_d80523e1_d80524e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$atan</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__section_w2964ab1b7b5_w2965ab1b7_w2966ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__p_d80525e1_d80526e1_d80527e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">vResult = $atan(1 / 2)</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__topic_d53012e1_d53013e1_d53014e1_d53015e1_d53016e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d408073e83\">Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__d6497e20\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>—numeric value.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__topic_d53017e1_d53018e1_d53019e1_d53020e1_d53021e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d408073e95\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__p_d80537e1_d80538e1_d80539e1\">Calculated arc tangent value.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__p_d80540e1_d80541e1_d80542e1\">If an error occurs, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> contains a negative value that identifies the exact error.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__topic_d53022e1_d53023e1_d53024e1_d53025e1_d53026e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d408073e111\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__topic_d53027e1_d53028e1_d53029e1_d53030e1_d53031e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d408073e120\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__p_d80552e1_d80553e1_d80554e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$atan</span> function calculates the arc tangent of <var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>, that is, it returns that angle, in radians, whose tangent (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$tan</span>) is <var class=\"keyword varname\">X</var>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__section_azb_xwx_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d408073e141\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$atan</span></h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example returns the arc tangent of the given\n            expression:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"ppd1665702781928__pre_yyh_xwx_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vResult = $atan(1 / 2)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwm1665702782002.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$tan</a><p>Return the tangent of X.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7423233\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7423233\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$atan Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 29, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Return the arc tangent of X. $atan ( X ) Example: vResult = $atan(1 / 2) Parameters X —numeric value. Return Values Calculated arc tangent value. If an error occurs, $procerror contains a negative value that identifies the exact error. Use Allowed in all component types. Description The $atan function calculates the arc tangent of X , that is, it returns that angle, in radians, whose tangent ( $tan ) is X . Example: Using $atan The following example returns the arc tangent of the given expression: vResult = $atan(1 / 2) Copy Related Links $tan Return the tangent of X. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}